{"questionId":"9076742","questionHtml":"<p>Show that about –11 C of charge is delivered to the Earth’s surface.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>Q</em> =&nbsp;<strong>«</strong><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{Q_0}{e^{ - \\frac{t}{\\tau }}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>Q</mi>\n      <mn>0</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>e</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mfrac>\n          <mi>t</mi>\n          <mi>τ</mi>\n        </mfrac>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;=<strong>»</strong> 25&nbsp;× <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{e^{ - \\frac{{18}}{{32}}}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>e</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mfrac>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>18</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>32</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </mfrac>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><em>Q</em> = 14.2&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>C<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>charge delivered =&nbsp;<em>Q</em> = 25 – 14.2 = 10.8&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>C<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p><strong>«</strong>≈ –11 C<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Final answer must be given to at least 3 significant figures</em></p>\n<p><strong><em>[3 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076742","referenceCode":"18M.2.HL.TZ2.c.i","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Show that about –11 C of charge is delivered to the Earth’s surface.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 11: Electromagnetic induction","11.3 – Capacitance","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 11: Electromagnetic induction"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}